search_results.title: Here Comes Everybody: The Story of the Pogues
search_results.snippet: The Pogues injected the fury of punk into Irish folk music and gave the world the troubled, iconic, darkly romantic songwriter Shane MacGowan.

search_results.title: The Pogues
search_results.snippet: The Pogues are an English Celtic punk band founded in King's Cross, London, in 1982, by Shane MacGowan, Spider Stacy and Jem Finer.
